<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>My thoughts (somewhat shorter reply)</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Argil">Argil</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:14 p.m. 19/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> My thoughts (somewhat shorter reply)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/veeshan.cgi?read=107" TARGET=_self>The Monopoly of Banded Mail will stop! This concerns ALL citizens of Norrath (lng txt)</A> (Kiron of Sacred Haven)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>First, let me say that I've never met either you or Shiron personally. I've exchanged "Hails" with a few Sacred Haven members, and I've been in zones when Shiron was selling, but that's it.

<P>I commend you for making this post openly rather than anonymously - that's done a great deal of that on the "other" message board (EQ Vault) and those posts are easily disregarded. You've obviously put a huge amount of thought and time into this post.
<P>Your post troubles me greatly, as I had never heard negative comments about Shiron previously. I had heard that he had established standard prices, but was not aware that he was coercing others into following them. I suppose it's a natural reflex to be a bit put out when someone undercuts your selling price, but Shiron's response, as you relate it, seems a bit over the top.
<P>I would encourage you to post your price list here, if you are willing and able to do so at this time. I agree that free and open competition will be best for all, especially the buyers of Norath!
<P>I also strongly encourage anyone who knows Shiron to ask him to do the same. This would seem to encourage the type of free exchange of information I think you're arguing for here.
<P>Lastly, should you and Shiron require an intermediary to arrive at some agreement or arrangement, I would gladly serve in that role for you.
<P>Thanks for an informative post; let's try to build on what you've started!
<P>Argil Silverlock
<BR>Magician of Faydwer
<BR>Lost Order of Akalabeth
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
